The paper deals with the compression of 3D point cloud sequences, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a graph-based approach to represent the time-varying geometry of the sequences, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves motion estimation and feature matching, which could be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.IT.
